<div class="container" style="margin-top: 25px">
	<div class="p-name" style="text-align:center">
		<h3 class="project-name-label">PROJECT: </h3>
		<h3 class="project-name">C.R. KANNAN</h3><br><br>
	</div>
	<hr/>
	<div class="links">
		<div class="link-image link-image-2">
			<%= link_to image_tag('misc/website.png'), 'http://crkannan.com/', target: '_blank' %>
		</div> 
	</div><br />
	<p class="highlights">"A Portfolio Website for a Professional Marketing Consultant"</p>
		<h3 class="project-deliverables" style="text-align: center; font-size: 30px; font-family: 'Raleway-Light', sans-serif">
			DELIVERABLES
		</h3><br />
		<div class="dev-project-roles">
			<div class="dev-role">PROTOTYPES</div>
			<div class="dev-role">RESPONSIVE WEBSITE</div>
			<div class="dev-role">ANALYTICS INTEGRATION</div>
		</div><br>
		<div class="jumbotron">
			<h3 class="dev-project-description-label">THE CLIENT'S REQUIREMENTS</h3>
				<p class="dev-project-description" style="margin-top: 10px">
					The client was a marketing consultant who wanted a website to show the history of their work along with all elements of their resume. The site needed to have a gallery page, a page with history of milestones, a resume page, an 'about me' page, and a contact page in addition to the landing page.
				</p>
				<p class="dev-project-description" style="margin-top: 10px">
					I built the website with Ruby as the primary backend language and Rails as the framework. In addition to using HTML5 and CSS3 elements, I also used several jQuery plugins to make the site more dynamic and interactive.
				</p>
		</div>
		<div class="jumbotron" style="background-color: #fff">
			<h3 class="dev-project-description-label">A VERY MINIMAL LANDING PAGE</h3>
			<div class="cem-listng-row">
				<div class="cem-listing">
					<%= image_tag('crk/layout-2.png') %>
				</div>
				<div class="cem-listing">
					<%= image_tag('crk/layout-1.png') %>
				</div>
			</div><br><br>
			<p class="dev-project-description" style="margin-top: 10px">
				The landing page has a very simple banner image that I edited with photoshop. I added the brand name at the top left and the headers to the top right. When a user hovers over any of the header, the background switches to an organge color to signify which option has been chosen.
			</p>
			<p class="dev-project-description" style="margin-top: 10px">
				I added the social links at the bottom right. When a user hovers over any of the social icons, they scale up to reveal which option has been chosen.
			</p>
			<p class="dev-project-description" style="margin-top: 10px">
				I was able to achieve this with only css. The hover function was very important because it added another level of interactivity to the website.
			</p><br>
		</div>
			<div class="jumbotron">
				<h3 class="dev-project-description-label">A DROP DOWN FOR EACH MILESTONE</h3>
					<div class="cem-listng-row">
				<div class="cem-listing">
					<%= image_tag('crk/layout-5.png') %>
				</div>
				<div class="cem-listing">
					<%= image_tag('crk/layout-6.png') %>
				</div>
			</div><br><br>
				<p class="dev-project-description" style="margin-top: 10px">
					The Milestones are reflected with each button (taken from bootstrap). The buttons are aligned in a vertical line to showcase a timeline.
				</p>
				<p class="dev-project-description" style="margin-top: 10px">
					Clicking on each button opens a grey-box that contains all the milestones pertaining to that year. The goal is to have ample amount of information without overcrowding.
				</p>
			</div>
				<div class="jumbotron" style="background-color: #fff">
			<h3 class="dev-project-description-label">A GALLERY TO HIGHLIGHT A RESUME</h3>
			<div class="cem-listng-row">
				<div class="cem-listing">
					<%= image_tag('crk/layout-7.png') %>
				</div>
				<div class="cem-listing">
					<%= image_tag('crk/layout-8.png') %>
				</div>
			</div><br><br>
			<p class="dev-project-description" style="margin-top: 10px">
				I decided to use a very old-fashioned design wiht the font and the overall layout to highlight that these milestones took place a lot of years. 
			</p>
			<p class="dev-project-description" style="margin-top: 10px">
				I broke down each set of images according to the specific category that they belong to.
			</p>
			<p class="dev-project-description" style="margin-top: 10px">
				Clicking on each image opens a zoomed version which I was able to achieve with the fancybox plugin.
			</p><br>
		</div>
